metadata.name: Laniakea #123
metadata.description:
This piece captures the mysterious beauty of the Laniakea Supercluster, the colossal cosmic structure that contains our Milky Way galaxy.

A deep black backdrop is scattered with shimmering stars, evoking a sense of endless space and awe-inspiring expanse. Winds of dark matter are captured in the mid-ground, representing the invisible force that drives the formation of the galaxies within the Supercluster.

The foreground features a small spiral galaxy, shining brightly against the backdrop of the universe, reminding us that we are an integral part of an unimaginably grand structure.

metadata.name: Trust #30
metadata.description:
Trust is an abstraction of the creative process, finding the line just before form becomes texture. Your experience with the painting requires trust; trust that something will appear from the chaos of the empty space, trust that the composition you imagine halfway through will evolve along with your ideas, and trust that the etchings lend a helping hand to the message of the piece. You may find yourself pulled left and right when decisions are made, and your interpretation at 25%, 50%, and 90% will all differ. This is what makes creating so fulfilling to me, a work of art can change course wildly from start to finish, ever molding itself until it enters the kiln.

metadata.name: tur1ng #112
metadata.description:
‚Äòtur1ng‚Äô consists of audible image architectures based on the principle of Turing machines. These systems are mathematical models of computation that manipulate symbols on a strip of tape according to a table of rules. The machine first writes a symbol in a cell on the tape, then either moves the tape one cell left or right, then, based on the observed symbol and the machine's own state in the table, either proceeds to another instruction or halts computation.

In ‚Äòtur1ng‚Äô, rules are stored as colors and the original tape cells are constructed from a two dimensional array. The sound unfolds as the algorithm proceeds: monitoring these binary songs requires being attentive to changes in the state or behavior of the system over time so that appropriate interventions or other process-related activities may be carried out. Another feature of listening algorithms is that it often has to be done as a background or secondary task or, perhaps, in parallel with one or more other primary tasks.

Touch to listen.

metadata.name: Brinco #81
metadata.description:
As slinkies rise and sway through flurries of confetti, sometimes this play is focused and orderly. At other times, they crowd together riotously, conspiring to sneak off the sides altogether.

"Brinco" (Portuguese for "I play") is about celebrating finding joy in my creative pursuits again; about not overthinking it and simply following what makes me happy.

Creative joy can be capricious, leaving us when we need it the most. We hope we can relate to our artistic practice in a positive way, tapping into what feels like a bottomless source of energy and excitement. But sometimes when life becomes overwhelming, what gave you energy before now feels hollow and rote‚Äîjust one more thing sapping at you, and an emptiness where creative passion once resided.

For over a year, I've been sitting in this shadow. Until one day, I sat down and started tinkering‚Ä¶ and for the first time in such a long time, I started to feel the spark.

I hope that viewers and collectors feel that same spark of joy and playfulness when seeing these pieces that I've felt creating them.

Press "s"/"S" to save a PNG at the current size and press "h"/"H" to save a high resolution version.

metadata.name: Chroma-Ville #94
metadata.description:
Each output is generated by layering Blender renders.

The prefix 'Chroma' refers to the large color palette used in the Chroma series.

'Chroma-Ville' is the final creation in the 'Chroma' series. The arrangement of cubes creates an image reminiscent of a city-scape. Coupled with the carefully balanced colors, each output forms a bold, striking design.

In live mode:
Click/tap the image to make a "Download image" button appear. Click this button to download a 1500x2000px PNG.

metadata.name: Monochrome Intersections #7
metadata.description:
I decided to do this version because Intersections created too many issues with the previews. I made a reserve list for all collectors of Intersections (this reserve list will be available during 1 week). I put a small price because of preview‚Äôs issues and I am really grateful to saw all my projects found collectors, and I don‚Äôt know how to tell you üôè
‚Ä®I also worked on a bug to fix the rendering on objkt.com.‚Ä®

Monochrome Intersections are a group of artworks creating organic and animated lines. A mix between digital renderings with colorful lines and a generated grid creating a paper-like visual.

Lines are animated with an infinite algorithm to create a mesmerizing animation. 
The pieces's size, position and frequency are generated for each token, along with the colour theme and the composition effect. 

You can click to play/pause the animation.

Features :
- Clip: triangle, circle or reversed triangle
- LinesCount: number of lines
- smallLines: boolean, if lines are thin or bold
- colorTheme: name of the color theme
- filter: Canvas composition effect applied : difference, multiply, xor, hard-light, source-over
- isDistorted: distortions enabled

‚Ä®Handmade by code with Javascript, made with fragment.tools
Quentin Hocd√©, Brussels (Belgium), 2023.

metadata.name: Traffic #151
metadata.description:
Traffic is a companion piece to Scaffold. Whilst Scaffold was intended to capture a moment in time of a single mind, Traffic aims to represent a shared moment in a community.

Outputs can be beautiful, but can also be chaotic. They can be comprised of many contributions, but a single voice may drown out many others.

All royalties go to the original minter.

Keyboard commands:

s - save as png
h - toggle high resolution‚Ä®
b - toggle background texture
a - switch aspect ratio
r - new moment

metadata.name: Millefoglie #262
metadata.description:
"A mille-feuille (French pronunciation: ‚Äã[mil f≈ìj], "thousand-sheets"), also known by the names Napoleon, vanilla slice, and custard slice, is a dessert made of puff pastry layered with pastry cream. Its modern form was influenced by improvements made by Marie-Antoine Car√™me.

Traditionally, a mille-feuille is made up of three layers of puff pastry (p√¢te feuillet√©e), alternating with two layers of pastry cream (cr√®me p√¢tissi√®re). The top pastry layer is finished in various ways: sometimes it is topped with whipped cream, or it may be dusted with icing sugar, cocoa, pastry crumbs, or sliced almonds. It may also be glazed with icing or fondant alone, or in alternating white (icing) and brown (chocolate) or other colored icing stripes, and combed to create a marbled effect." ‚Äî Wikipedia
